  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n---\n## 2026-04-01 04:13 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 4] Funding Rate Squeeze Signal: Built Detector + Funding-vs-WR Correlation\n\n**Task:** Build a BTC funding rate squeeze detector and correlate funding regimes with PM trading performance.\n\n**Finding:**\n1. **Funding squeeze detector LIVE** \u2014 `intelligence/funding-squeeze-detector.py` on cron */30. Scores SHORT_SQUEEZE/LONG_SQUEEZE probability 0-100 using: funding rate streak, deepening acceleration, L/S ratio trend.\n2. **Current score: 61/100 SHORT_SQUEEZE** \u2014 3-period negative streak (-0.0019% \u2192 -0.0028% \u2192 -0.0034%), deepening confirmed, L/S ratio declining 16.9% over 12h (1.898 \u2192 1.577). Textbook squeeze setup.\n3. **Funding vs PM WR (all data, n=164):** Long-funding days = 61% WR (n=106), Short-funding days = 43% WR (n=58). **18pp delta AGAINST our thesis!** But this is contaminated by pre-V3 garbage (bad hours, NO trades, 24h trading).\n4. **V3+ era (Mar 27+, n=17):** Too small to be conclusive. Short-funding: 6W/3L = 67% WR. Long-funding: 5W/2L = 71% WR. Nearly identical. Signal is noise at this sample size.\n5. **Key insight: funding regime \u2260 5-min PM edge.** Funding rates reflect 8h positioning. PM 5-min markets resolve in 5 minutes. The timescale mismatch means funding likely doesn't predict individual 5-min outcomes \u2014 it predicts daily BTC direction, which our contrarian bot already adapts to via bias signal.\n\n**My thinking:**\n- The pre-V3 correlation (SHORT=43%, LONG=61%) is likely explained by: short-funding days = BTC dropping = pre-V3 bot trading bad hours and NO direction = losing. It's not that funding predicts PM outcomes \u2014 it's that market conditions that cause negative funding also cause our old unfiltered bot to lose.\n- Post-V3, the signal washes out because our filters already handle regime. The V4.1 regime filter blocks TREND days, which is the real mechanism \u2014 not funding rate per se.\n- **Decision: DON'T wire funding into bot conviction yet.** The squeeze detector is useful as a dashboard/research signal, not as a trading filter. Keep accumulating V3+ data. Revisit at n\u226550 trades with funding correlation.\n- The squeeze detector output (`squeeze-funding.json`) is available for V6 consideration if data proves it matters.\n\n**Decision:**\n- Funding squeeze detector deployed as OBSERVATIONAL tool only\n- pm_adjustment field exists but set conservatively (+0.10 at 60+, +0.05 at 40+)\n- Will NOT integrate into V5a/V5b \u2014 needs minimum 50-trade V3+ sample first\n- Current 61/100 SHORT_SQUEEZE = bullish context for today's active hours (directional bias, not trade filter)\n\n**Next:** P1 \u2014 Copy Intelligence. Check if any human traders have appeared on PM daily/weekly markets (V6 opportunity from yesterday's finding).\n\n---\n## 2026-04-01 04:08 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 3] V5a Deploy Prep: Shadow Validator Built + Overnight Market Analysis\n\n**Task:** Build real-time V5a validation tooling for active hours and analyze overnight setup for",
